<section sectnbr = "6C">
<servcat sctnbr = "06" scnbr = "03">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "4">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "S8T40A6304002" svcinfotypenbr = "06" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Steering Wheel Check
</title>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Check steering wheel for looseness or rattle by trying to move it in its shaft direction and lateral direction.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If found defective, repair or replace.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Check steering wheel for play, holding car in straight forward condition on the ground and with engine stopped.
</ptxt>
<spec-sdm>
<sdm-title>
Steering wheel play
</sdm-title>
<sdm-part>
&#8220;a&#8221;
</sdm-part>
<sdm1>
<sdm-condition>
</sdm-condition>
<sdm-value>
0 &#8211; 30 mm (0 &#8211; 1.2 in.)
</sdm-value>
</sdm1>
</spec-sdm>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5JB0A630004.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "53.498mm" ver = "02" gw = "187" gh = "135"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>
If steering wheel play is not within specification, inspect as follows and replace if found defective.
</ptxt>
</item>
<list2 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Tie-rod end ball stud for wear
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Lower ball joint for wear
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Steering shaft joint for wear
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Steering pinion or rack gear for wear or breakage
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Each part for looseness
</ptxt>
</item>
</list2>
</list1>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
